race.comment: ALL ABOUT ARTIE (4) is back from a 15-week spell. Closed last prep with four consecutive minor placings, all at longer trips than this. Will be better for the run but while fresh from the inside gate he should be popular with punters. NAILS AND PRIDE (2) found the lead a fair way from home and kept going to record a tough win over 1400m at Grafton recently. Has his share of weight but should be competitive again. WEST CORK (5) just felt the pinch at the end of 1400m against better company at the Gold Coast last time. Can improve in this more suitable assignment. DOYLE (12) is ready to show something at the third run back from a spell.
